{
  "name": "Serpent Fang Double",
  "type": "spell",
  "img": "systems/n5eb/assets/Icons%20%26%20Images/Icons/Taijutsu.png",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>As a requirement to activate this jutsu, you must currently be in the Serpent Fist Stance.</p><p>You enter a low striking stance showing your overwhelming focus and precision as you disable your opponent with surgical accuracy. Make two melee taijutsu attacks dealing your [Unarmed Damage] + 1d8. A creature who is hit by at least one of these attacks, must make a Constitution saving throw. On a failed save they gain +1 rank of Weakened.</p><p>If this jutsu is used as a Finisher, you instead deal your [Unarmed Damage] + 1d12 and if you score two hits on the target, they must make a Constitution saving throw, gaining +2 rank of Weakened on a failed save.</p><p>At Higher Ranks: For each rank you cast this jutsu above D-Rank increase the cost of this jutsu by 3 and the damage by 1d8 or 1d12.</p>",
      "chat": ""
    },
